instructions:
Ingredients:
- 1/2 lb. beefs
- 1 head of fresh broccoli
- 1 onions
- 1 carrot
- 2 tablespoons of olive oil
- Salt and pepper, to taste
Instructions:
1. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
2. Slice beef into thin strips and add to the skillet. 
3. Cook the beef until it begins to brown, stirring occasionally.
4. Peel and finely chop onion and carrots.
5. Add freshly chopped onions and carrots to the skillet and stir.
6. Break apart the broccoli florets and add it to the mix.
7. Cook until broccoli is tender and vegetables are cooked through, stirring frequently.
8. Add salt and pepper to season.
9. Serve beef and broccoli stir fry with rice or noodles and enjoy.
title: Beef and Broccoli Stirfry

instructions:
Ingredients:
- 2 medium apples, peeled, cored, and diced
- 2 oranges, peeled and diced
- 2 medium potatoes, peeled and diced
- 2 tablespoons unsalted butter
- 1 teaspoon sugar
- Salt and pepper to taste

Testing adding word

Instructions:
1. Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat.

2. Add the potatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and nearly cooked through, about 8 minutes.

3. Add the apples and oranges and cook for 3 minutes more.

4. Stir in the sugar and season with salt and pepper to taste.

5. Continue to cook until the potatoes and fruit are tender, about 5 minutes more.

6. Serve warm. Enjoy!
title: Breakfast Fruit and Potato Hash

instructions:
Ingredients: 
-1 cup cooked salmon, cubed
-2 cups spinach
-2 large tomatoes, chopped
-1/4 cup basil, chopped
-1/4 cup parsley, chopped
-2 tablespoons cilantro, chopped
-1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil
-2 tablespoons lemon juice
-Sea Salt, to taste

Instructions: 
1. Place cooked salmon, spinach, tomatoes, basil, parsley, and cilantro in a large bowl and mix together.

2. In a small bowl, mix together extra virgin olive oil, lemon juice and sea salt.

3. Pour the olive oil mixture over the salad and mix together.

4. Serve and enjoy!
title: Salmon Super Salad

instructions:
Ingredients:
- 2 large eggs
- 2 cups fresh spinach
- Olive oil
- Salt and pepper to taste 

Instructions:
1. Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and add some olive oil.
2. Once the oil is hot, add the spinach and cook until wilted, about 2 minutes.
3. Crack the eggs into the pan over the spinach.
4. Cook until the eggs are cooked through to desired preference–-scrambled lightly, or cooked through entirely.
5. Season with salt and pepper to taste. 
6. Serve warm and enjoy!
title: Spinach and Egg Breakfast Bowl
